[build] Always use unzip for non-Windows hosts

GNU tar (Linux default) cannot read `.zip` archives. bsdtar (macOS) can,
but it silently turns symlinks in `.zip` into zero-byte files which then
fail as `posix_spawn: Exec format error` (the NDK has many symlinks).
Both problems are avoided by simply using `unzip` everywhere on Unix.

Drop the `UseUnzipOnUnix` per-item opt-in metadata and key the extraction
strategy purely on `HostOS`:

  * Windows: `tar -xf` (bsdtar handles .zip with `--strip-components`).
  * Unix:    `unzip` into a sibling `.staging` directory + `find ... mv`.

